    "imageURL": null,
    "description": "A genuine must-visit and one of the great country houses of America. The six-story stone mansion sits on a hill above the Hudson with views that explain precisely why four generations of Rockefellers never left. But the house is almost secondary to what's outside: Nelson Rockefeller filled the terraced gardens with an extraordinary collection of 20th-century sculpture — Picasso, Calder, Brancusi, Giacometti, Henry Moore — arranged as casually as garden ornaments. The underground art galleries beneath the coach barn contain serious works by de Kooning, Warhol, and Léger. Tours are run through Historic Hudson Valley and book up well in advance; plan accordingly. This is one of the best single sites in the entire Hudson Valley.",
